Report ethical violations



Ameriprise Financial is committed to maintaining the highest standards of ethical business conduct. We promote a work environment that fosters mutual respect, openness and integrity. We achieve these goals by having policies and resources in place to guide individuals making ethical business decisions to support our mission and values.
Leaders, employees, advisors, independent contractors and vendors
The Ethics Hotline is a resource for leaders, employees, advisors, independent contractors and vendors. If you would like to report a suspected ethics violation, call the Ethics Hotline at 800.963.6395.
The Ethics Hotline is available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week and is run by an independent third party. The hotline allows callers to remain anonymous and provides a comprehensive and confidential reporting service that assists leaders, employees, advisors, independent contractors and vendors with to addressing ethical concerns and misconduct in the workplace.
Clients
Clients may report suspected ethical violations to the Ameriprise Financial Compliance Department at 866.738.5934 or at the address noted below:
Ameriprise Financial
2923 Ameriprise Financial Center H26/2923
Minneapolis, MN 55474




































